## Method 1: Upload via GitHub Website (Easiest)

### If you don't have a repository yet:

1. Go to [GitHub](https://github.com) and log in
2. Click the **"+"** icon in the top right corner
3. Select **"New repository"**
4. Enter repository name (e.g., "CurrencyExchanger")
5. Choose Public or Private
6. **Check** "Add a README file"
7. Click **"Create repository"**
8. Click on the **README.md** file
9. Click the **pencil icon** (Edit this file)
10. Delete the default content
11. Copy and paste your README content from `README.md`
12. Scroll down and click **"Commit changes"**

### If you already have a repository:

1. Go to your repository on GitHub
2. Click **"Add file"** → **"Upload files"**
3. Drag and drop the `README.md` file from your project folder
4. Or click **"choose your files"** and select `README.md`
5. Add a commit message (e.g., "Add comprehensive README")
6. Click **"Commit changes"**

## Method 2: Using Git Command Line (If you want to sync later)

```bash
# Navigate to your project directory
cd C:/Users/jbane/AndroidStudioProjects/CurrencyExchanger

# Initialize git (if not already done)
git init

# Add only the README file
git add README.md

# Commit the README
git commit -m "Add comprehensive README documentation"

# Add your GitHub repository as remote (replace with your actual repo URL)
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/CurrencyExchanger.git

# Push only the README
git push -u origin main
```

## Method 3: Copy-Paste Content Directly

1. Open your local `README.md` file in a text editor
2. Copy all the content (Ctrl+A, Ctrl+C)
3. Go to your GitHub repository
4. Click **"Add file"** → **"Create new file"**
5. Name the file `README.md`
6. Paste the content (Ctrl+V)
7. Scroll down and click **"Commit new file"**

